"\t\t\t.mapProperties(Person.class)\n"
"\t\t\t.all();\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:276
#, no-wrap
msgid "What about `null`?"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:285
msgid ""
"Relational database results can contain `null` values.  The Reactive Streams "
"specification forbids the emission of `null` values.  That requirement "
"mandates proper `null` handling in the extractor function.  While you can "
"obtain `null` values from a `Row`, you must not emit a `null` value. You "
"must wrap any `null` values in an object (for example, `Optional` for "
"singular values) to make sure a `null` value is never returned directly by "
"your extractor function."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:288
#, no-wrap
msgid "Updating (`INSERT`, `UPDATE`, and `DELETE`) with `DatabaseClient`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:292
msgid ""
"The only difference of modifying statements is that these statements "
"typically do not return tabular data so you use `rowsUpdated()` to consume "
"results."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:295
msgid ""
"The following example shows an `UPDATE` statement that returns the number of "
"updated rows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:305
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tMono<Integer> affectedRows = client.sql(\"UPDATE person SET first_name = "
":fn\")\n"
"\t\t\t.bind(\"fn\", \"Joe\")\n"
"\t\t\t.fetch().rowsUpdated();\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:314
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tval affectedRows = client.sql(\"UPDATE person SET first_name = :fn\")\n"
"\t\t\t.bind(\"fn\", \"Joe\")\n"
"\t\t\t.fetch().awaitRowsUpdated()\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:318
#, no-wrap
msgid "Binding Values to Queries"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:329
msgid ""
"A typical application requires parameterized SQL statements to select or "
"update rows according to some input. These are typically `SELECT` statements "
"constrained by a `WHERE` clause or `INSERT` and `UPDATE` statements that "
"accept input parameters. Parameterized statements bear the risk of SQL "
"injection if parameters are not escaped properly. `DatabaseClient` leverages "
"R2DBC's `bind` API to eliminate the risk of SQL injection for query "
"parameters.  You can provide a parameterized SQL statement with the "
"`execute(…)` operator and bind parameters to the actual `Statement`. Your "
"R2DBC driver then runs the statement by using prepared statements and "
"parameter substitution."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:331
msgid "Parameter binding supports two binding strategies:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:333
msgid "By Index, using zero-based parameter indexes."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:334
msgid "By Name, using the placeholder name."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:336
msgid "The following example shows parameter binding for a query:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:343
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tdb.sql(\"INSERT INTO person (id, name, age) VALUES(:id, :name, :age)\")\n"
"\t\t\t.bind(\"id\", \"joe\")\n"
"\t\t\t.bind(\"name\", \"Joe\")\n"
"\t\t\t.bind(\"age\", 34);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:346
msgid "Alternatively, you may pass in a map of names and values:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:355
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tMap<String, Object> params = new LinkedHashMap<>();\n"
"\tparams.put(\"id\", \"joe\");\n"
"\tparams.put(\"name\", \"Joe\");\n"
"\tparams.put(\"age\", 34);\n"
"\tdb.sql(\"INSERT INTO person (id, name, age) VALUES(:id, :name, :age)\")\n"
"\t\t\t.bindValues(params);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:358
msgid ""
"Or you may pass in a parameter object with bean properties or record "
"components:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:364
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t// assuming id, name, age properties on Person\n"
"\tdb.sql(\"INSERT INTO person (id, name, age) VALUES(:id, :name, :age)\")\n"
"\t\t\t.bindProperties(new Person(\"joe\", \"Joe\", 34);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:368
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can use positional parameters for binding values to "
"statements.  Indices are zero based."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:375
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tdb.sql(\"INSERT INTO person (id, name, age) VALUES(:id, :name, :age)\")\n"
"\t\t\t.bind(0, \"joe\")\n"
"\t\t\t.bind(1, \"Joe\")\n"
"\t\t\t.bind(2, 34);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:378
msgid ""
"In case your application is binding to many parameters, the same can be "
"achieved with a single call:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:384
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tList<?> values = List.of(\"joe\", \"Joe\", 34);\n"
"\tdb.sql(\"INSERT INTO person (id, name, age) VALUES(:id, :name, :age)\")\n"
"\t\t\t.bindValues(values);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:388
#, no-wrap
msgid "R2DBC Native Bind Markers"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:393
msgid ""
"R2DBC uses database-native bind markers that depend on the actual database "
"vendor.  As an example, Postgres uses indexed markers, such as `$1`, `$2`, "
"`$n`.  Another example is SQL Server, which uses named bind markers prefixed "
"with `@`."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:397
msgid ""
"This is different from JDBC which requires `?` as bind markers.  In JDBC, "
"the actual drivers translate `?` bind markers to database-native markers as "
"part of their statement execution."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:400
msgid ""
"Spring Framework's R2DBC support lets you use native bind markers or named "
"bind markers with the `:name` syntax."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:404
msgid ""
"Named parameter support leverages a `BindMarkersFactory` instance to expand "
"named parameters to native bind markers at the time of query execution, "
"which gives you a certain degree of query portability across various "
"database vendors."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:409
msgid ""
"The query-preprocessor unrolls named `Collection` parameters into a series "
"of bind markers to remove the need of dynamic query creation based on the "
"number of arguments.  Nested object arrays are expanded to allow usage of "
"(for example) select lists."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:411
msgid "Consider the following query:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:415
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"SELECT id, name, state FROM table WHERE (name, age) IN (('John', 35), "
"('Ann', 50))\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:418
msgid "The preceding query can be parameterized and run as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:428
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tList<Object[]> tuples = new ArrayList<>();\n"
"\ttuples.add(new Object[] {\"John\", 35});\n"
"\ttuples.add(new Object[] {\"Ann\",  50});\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:431
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tclient.sql(\"SELECT id, name, state FROM table WHERE (name, age) IN "
"(:tuples)\")\n"
"\t\t\t.bind(\"tuples\", tuples);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:440
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tval tuples: MutableList<Array<Any>> = ArrayList()\n"
"\ttuples.add(arrayOf(\"John\", 35))\n"
"\ttuples.add(arrayOf(\"Ann\", 50))\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:443
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tclient.sql(\"SELECT id, name, state FROM table WHERE (name, age) IN "
"(:tuples)\")\n"
"\t\t\t.bind(\"tuples\", tuples)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:447
msgid "Usage of select lists is vendor-dependent."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:449
msgid "The following example shows a simpler variant using `IN` predicates:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:458
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tclient.sql(\"SELECT id, name, state FROM table WHERE age IN (:ages)\")\n"
"\t\t\t.bind(\"ages\", Arrays.asList(35, 50));\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:466
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tclient.sql(\"SELECT id, name, state FROM table WHERE age IN (:ages)\")\n"
"\t\t\t.bind(\"ages\", arrayOf(35, 50))\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:476
msgid ""
"R2DBC itself does not support Collection-like values. Nevertheless, "
"expanding a given `List` in the example above works for named parameters in "
"Spring's R2DBC support, for example, for use in `IN` clauses as shown "
"above.  However, inserting or updating array-typed columns (for example, in "
"Postgres)  requires an array type that is supported by the underlying R2DBC "
"driver: typically a Java array, for example, `String[]` to update a `text[]` "
"column.  Do not pass `Collection<String>` or the like as an array parameter."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:478
#, no-wrap
msgid "Statement Filters"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:484
msgid ""
"Sometimes you need to fine-tune options on the actual `Statement` before it "
"gets run. To do so, register a `Statement` filter "
"(`StatementFilterFunction`) with the `DatabaseClient` to intercept and "
"modify statements in their execution, as the following example shows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:495
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tclient.sql(\"INSERT INTO table (name, state) VALUES(:name, :state)\")\n"
"\t\t\t.filter((s, next) -> next.execute(s.returnGeneratedValues(\"id\")))\n"
"\t\t\t.bind(\"name\", …)\n"
"\t\t\t.bind(\"state\", …);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:505
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tclient.sql(\"INSERT INTO table (name, state) VALUES(:name, :state)\")\n"
"\t\t\t.filter { s: Statement, next: ExecuteFunction -> "
"next.execute(s.returnGeneratedValues(\"id\")) }\n"
"\t\t\t.bind(\"name\", …)\n"
"\t\t\t.bind(\"state\", …)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:510
msgid ""
"`DatabaseClient` also exposes a simplified `filter(…)` overload that accepts "
"a `Function<Statement, Statement>`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:519
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tclient.sql(\"INSERT INTO table (name, state) VALUES(:name, :state)\")\n"
"\t\t\t.filter(statement -> s.returnGeneratedValues(\"id\"));\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:522
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tclient.sql(\"SELECT id, name, state FROM table\")\n"
"\t\t\t.filter(statement -> s.fetchSize(25));\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:530
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tclient.sql(\"INSERT INTO table (name, state) VALUES(:name, :state)\")\n"
"\t\t\t.filter { statement -> s.returnGeneratedValues(\"id\") }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:533
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tclient.sql(\"SELECT id, name, state FROM table\")\n"
"\t\t\t.filter { statement -> s.fetchSize(25) }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:538
msgid ""
"`StatementFilterFunction` implementations allow filtering of the `Statement` "
"and filtering of `Result` objects."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:540
#, no-wrap
msgid "`DatabaseClient` Best Practices"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:547
msgid ""
"Instances of the `DatabaseClient` class are thread-safe, once "
"configured. This is important because it means that you can configure a "
"single instance of a `DatabaseClient` and then safely inject this shared "
"reference into multiple DAOs (or repositories).  The `DatabaseClient` is "
"stateful, in that it maintains a reference to a `ConnectionFactory`, but "
"this state is not conversational state."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:552
msgid ""
"A common practice when using the `DatabaseClient` class is to configure a "
"`ConnectionFactory` in your Spring configuration file and then "
"dependency-inject that shared `ConnectionFactory` bean into your DAO "
"classes. The `DatabaseClient` is created in the setter for the "
"`ConnectionFactory`. This leads to DAOs that resemble the following:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:561
#, no-wrap
msgid "\tpublic class R2dbcCorporateEventDao implements CorporateEventDao {\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:563
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:602
#, no-wrap
msgid "\t\tprivate DatabaseClient databaseClient;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:567
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t\tpublic void setConnectionFactory(ConnectionFactory connectionFactory) "
"{\n"
"\t\t\tthis.databaseClient = DatabaseClient.create(connectionFactory);\n"
"\t\t}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:570
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:582
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:610
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:626
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t\t// R2DBC-backed implementations of the methods on the CorporateEventDao "
"follow...\n"
"\t}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:577
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tclass R2dbcCorporateEventDao(connectionFactory: ConnectionFactory) : "
"CorporateEventDao {\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:579
#, no-wrap
msgid "\t\tprivate val databaseClient = DatabaseClient.create(connectionFactory)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:590
msgid ""
"An alternative to explicit configuration is to use component-scanning and "
"annotation support for dependency injection. In this case, you can annotate "
"the class with `@Component` (which makes it a candidate for "
"component-scanning) and annotate the `ConnectionFactory` setter method with "
"`@Autowired`. The following example shows how to do so:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:600
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t@Component // <1>\n"
"\tpublic class R2dbcCorporateEventDao implements CorporateEventDao {\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:607
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t\t@Autowired // <2>\n"
"\t\tpublic void setConnectionFactory(ConnectionFactory connectionFactory) "
"{\n"
"\t\t\tthis.databaseClient = DatabaseClient.create(connectionFactory); // "
"<3>\n"
"\t\t}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:612
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:628
msgid "Annotate the class with `@Component`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/r2dbc.adoc:613
msgid "Annotate the `ConnectionFactory` setter method with `@Autowired`."
msgstr ""

